  "notes": "Amharic Ethiopic (Ge'ez) script. Abugida where each character encodes consonant + vowel; 7 vowel orders per consonant row. Ejectives: TКј, ДҢКј, PКј, TsКј are phonemic. The 6th order (Йҷ-vowel) is the inherent vowel. Г„, К• (Ayin) present in traditional script but may be realized as /К”/ or silent in colloquial speech.",
